title: Grateful Dead Live at Deer Creek Music Center on 1994-07-21
lineage: Unknown Mics > DAT > CDR > EAC 0.9 > CD Wave > SHN
description: Touch Of Grey, Greatest Story Ever Told, Jack A Roe, The Same Thing, Stagger Lee, Me & My Uncle->*, Mexicali Blues*, Ramble On Rose, The Music Never Stopped Women Are Smarter, If The Shoe Fits, Way to Go Home, Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower-> Drums-> Space-> All Along The Watchtower-> The Days Between-> Good Lovin', E: Liberty

reviews.review_text: Harbinger? Good show but....if I recall correctly....there was a helicopter hovering over the place as the band kicked into 'Watchtower'. Were the karma gods getting ready for the '95 fiasco?  Second set H>S>F rocked.
watchtower my first and only Dead show (thanks anissa) so very reassurring to see my wind memory collaborated...
number 82 of 89 What a great time. little did I know it would all be over soon. I think its grate they allow us to do this.

Deer Creek I think listening to anything from Deer Creek is great.  I live in Indianapolis so i have many of my lifes greatest memories there and I love to hear as much music from there as I can get a hold of.

H>S>F     This was my birthday show when I turned 23. Great memories of the whole weekend. I went alone from Chicago for the 3 shows and this guy at my campground would play the entire shows back at the campground every night several of us with our portable dat recorders would patch in. During Help on the way several of us jumped into the seats from the lawn. Really great H>S>F and great weekend. The only time I saw the band on my birthday. I knew how amazing this was at the time and I still know it now.

Help>Slip to Save the Day I was at this 3-night run and admittedly was pretty wiped for this show after all the fun from the night before (an all-time favorite show/day of my life). I was literally falling asleep despite fighting it during the Long Way, and thinking this might be the worst 2nd set of my life, and then from nowhere comes the familiar tuning riff of Help on the Way, my all-time favorite Dead tune and a Deer Creek staple (still pissed about those gate-crashers ruining the one we WOULD HAVE heard on 7/3/95). Days Between was nice and I remember a long (as far as # of tunes) if unspectacular 1st set. I would be curious to see how I'd feel about this show if I was at full energy though.
